text.tspan: A simple mental model for chaining transforms: Global frame

flowRoot.flowPara: Disclamer: In most use cases there is no need for chaining transforms manually in Godot. Manual transform chaining mainly arises in advanced use cases like procedural mesh generation or as a performance optimization when working with multi mesh instances. When possible, use the hierarchic nature of the node tree instead of worrying about manual transform chaining.

Image modeling a spinning tea cups ride as shown on the right. As a performance optimization we want to render all the tea cups using a multi mesh instance, in order to reduce the rendering to a single draw call instead of N draw calls, when modeling the scene traditionally with N cup nodes in the node tree.
